examples.text: Uzun ince bir yoldayım / Gidiyorum gündüz gece / Bilmiyorum ne haldeyim / Gidiyorum gündüz gece
examples.translation: I am on a long, thin road / I go day and night / I do not know what state I am in / I go day and night
This street leads to the coast.

glosses: to suit; to be suitable or apt for one's image

examples.translation: The poor man who was hit by the car passed away right there.

examples.text: Bu telefon bana üç yıl gitti.
examples.translation: This phone lasted me three years.

glosses: to be traded at a certain rate

examples.translation: At what rate is the dollar trading today?

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish كتمك (gitmek), from Proto-Turkic *kē(y)t- (“to go (away)”). Cognate of Azerbaijani getmək, Uzbek ketmoq, Kazakh кету (ketu) etc.
